    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$ I_{3}^{-} $is linear with central iodine atom undergoing $ s p^{3} d $-hybridisation and three lone pairs occupying equatorial position.</p><p>Thus, this structure include $ d $-orbital contribution to the hybridisation scheme.</p><p>The structure is,</p><p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7m7ojju/16387a4b-d818-492e-ab3d-8acd6c41136f/33f6d5a0-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7ojjv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7m7ojju/16387a4b-d818-492e-ab3d-8acd6c41136f/33f6d5a0-f46a-11ef-bbe5-33f4ad49c5b5/file-jaoe38c1m7m7ojjv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2024 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 2 English Explanation\"></p><p>$ \\mathrm{PCl}_{3} $ structure is $ s p^{3} $-hybridised with one lone pair. $ \\mathrm{NO}_{3}^{-} $is $ s p^{2} $-hybridised and $ \\mathrm{H}_{2} \\mathrm{Se} $ is $ s p^{3} $ - hybridised with two lone pairs of Se atom.</p>",
