  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>In $$\\mathrm{BrF}_3$$ molecule, the lone pairs occupy equatorial positions to minimise</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "lone pair-bond pair repulsion only\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "bond pair-bond pair repulsion only\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "lone pair-lone pair repulsion and lone pair-bond pair repulsion\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "lone pair-lone pair repulsion only"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>In $$\\mathrm{BrF}_3$$ molecule, $$\\mathrm{Br}$$ is $$s p^3 d$$ hybridised, but geometry is T-shaped due to distortion of geometry from trigonal-bipyramidal to T-shaped by the involvement of lone pair-lone pair repulsion. The lone pair occupies equitorial position in order to minimize lone pair-lone pair and lone pair-bond pair repulsion.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5i4nf9/c75b8fda-aef9-4cc1-bcae-4c4c66c3fd45/925d4c50-253f-11ef-8199-1df4a78b8ad5/file-jaoe38c1lx5i4nfa.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5i4nf9/c75b8fda-aef9-4cc1-bcae-4c4c66c3fd45/925d4c50-253f-11ef-8199-1df4a78b8ad5/file-jaoe38c1lx5i4nfa.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 5 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Here,</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{array}{l}l p-l p \\text { repulsion }=1 \\\\ l p-b p \\text { repulsion }=2 \\\\ b p-b p \\text { repulsion }=2\\end{array}$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
  {
    "comprehension": null,
    "direction": null,
    "content": "<p>Which one of the following is/are linear structure?</p>\n<p>I. $$\\mathrm{I}_3^{-}$$</p>\n<p>II. $$\\mathrm{NO}_2^{-}$$</p>\n<p>III. $$\\mathrm{I}_3^{+}$$</p>\n<p>IV. $$\\mathrm{SO}_2$$</p>\n<p>V. $$\\mathrm{N}_3^{-}$$</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "I, II and III"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "I and V"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "II, III and IV"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "All of these"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>$$\\mathrm{I}_3^{-}$$ ion is made up of an $$\\mathrm{I}_2$$ molecule with an $$\\mathrm{I}^{-}$$ bonded to it by means of a coordinate bond in which $$\\mathrm{I}_2$$ is lone pair acceptor (Lewis acid) and $$I^{-}$$ is lone pair donor (Lewis base).</p>\n<p>There are two bond pairs and three lone pairs in the outer shell of central atom. To minimise the repulsive forces the three lone pairs occupy the equatorial position.</p>\n<p>The ion is therefore, linear in shape with a bond angle of exactly $$180^{\\circ}$$.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1lx5iw693/ac4582f9-65db-4394-bded-45519351e22a/8fc18b70-2542-11ef-967d-7bb8a1750de0/file-jaoe38c1lx5iw694.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1lx5iw693/ac4582f9-65db-4394-bded-45519351e22a/8fc18b70-2542-11ef-967d-7bb8a1750de0/file-jaoe38c1lx5iw694.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"BITSAT 2023 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 4 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$\n\\underset{\\substack{\\text { Lewis } \\\\ \\text { acid }}}{\\mathrm{I}_2}+\\underset{\\substack{\\text { Lewis } \\\\ \\text { base }}}{\\mathrm{I}^{-}} \\longrightarrow[\\mathrm{I}-\\mathrm{I} \\leftarrow \\mathrm{I}]^{-}$$</p>\n<p>Similarly, $$\\mathrm{N}_3^{-}$$ ion is also linear in shape. $$\\mathrm{I}_3^{+}$$ does not have linear structure.</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
