    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lhygf3j3/5f427312-0b41-4b75-9d7b-1b5f43003bbc/27691a00-f868-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhygf3j4.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lhygf3j3/5f427312-0b41-4b75-9d7b-1b5f43003bbc/27691a00-f868-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhygf3j4.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2022 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 9 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>This is one unpaired electron in (O$$-$$F), hence, paramagnetic, thus (a) is correct.</p>\n<p>As bond order of O$$-$$F &gt; F$$-$$F thus, bond energy of O$$-$$F &gt; F$$-$$F.</p>\n<p>Hence, (a) and (b) both are correct.</p>",
