    "explanation": "<p>Hydrogen peroxide (H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub>) is a non-planar molecule with twisted symmetrical structure. It has non-linear structure with an open book structure.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lhyggqbo/3beb9b26-26de-49d7-9ac4-af60690ab80c/54d3b040-f868-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhyggqbp.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lhyggqbo/3beb9b26-26de-49d7-9ac4-af60690ab80c/54d3b040-f868-11ed-a462-b137e84afc65/file-1lhyggqbp.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2022 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 7 English Explanation\"></p>",
