    "correct_options": [
      "B"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Molecular electronic configuration for given species are</p>\n<p>(a) $${O_2} = \\sigma \\,1{s^2}\\,\\sigma *1{s^2}\\,\\sigma 2{s^2}\\,\\sigma *2{s^2}\\,\\sigma 2p_x^2\\,\\pi \\,2p_y^2\\,\\pi \\,2p_z^2\\,\\pi *2p_y^1\\,\\pi *2p_z^1$$</p>\n<p>It has two unpaired electrons.</p>\n<p>(b) $$O_2^{2 - }$$ : It has no unpaired electron.</p>\n<p>(c) $$N_2^{2 + }$$ : It has one unpaired electron.</p>\n<p>(d) B<sub>2</sub> : It has two unpaired electrons.</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ $$O_2^{2 - }$$ is diamagnetic in nature.</p>",
