    "explanation": "<p>Bond order for the various compounds are as follows</p>\n<p>for SO<sub>2</sub>,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lbwr8uho/914b7153-3866-4397-9459-c2284d9cc115/a06bb9c0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwr8uhp.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lbwr8uho/914b7153-3866-4397-9459-c2284d9cc115/a06bb9c0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwr8uhp.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2021 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 14 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Number of bonds = 4</p>\n<p>Number of (SO) groups = 2</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Bond order $$ = {4 \\over 2} = 2$$</p>\n<p>For SO<sub>3</sub>,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lbwr9j7f/2c4def21-c7e4-4e4c-bd6d-f196c6fd0886/b38344b0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwr9j7g.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lbwr9j7f/2c4def21-c7e4-4e4c-bd6d-f196c6fd0886/b38344b0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwr9j7g.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2021 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 14 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Number of bonds = 6</p>\n<p>Number of (SO) groups = 3</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Bond order $$ = {6 \\over 3} = 2$$</p>\n<p>For SO$$_4^{2 - }$$,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lbwra1wo/f2aed411-ea02-4e57-9de7-c2e796ddfc46/c1f5d8a0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwra1wq.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lbwra1wo/f2aed411-ea02-4e57-9de7-c2e796ddfc46/c1f5d8a0-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwra1wq.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2021 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 14 English Explanation 3\"></p>\n<p>Number of bonds = 6</p>\n<p>Number of (SO) groups = 4</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Bond order $$ = {6 \\over 4} = 1.5$$</p>\n<p>For SO$$_3^{2 - }$$,</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lbwrarxs/db5132f1-4b15-411e-b056-08f969912e31/d6113f00-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwrarxt.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lbwrarxs/db5132f1-4b15-411e-b056-08f969912e31/d6113f00-80af-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwrarxt.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2021 Chemistry - Chemical Bonding and Molecular Structure Question 14 English Explanation 4\"></p>\n<p>Number of bonds = 4</p>\n<p>Number of (SO) groups = 3</p>\n<p>$$\\therefore$$ Bond order $$ = {4 \\over 3} = 1.33$$</p>\n<p>Hence, correct order is $$S{O_2} = S{O_3} &gt; SO_4^{2 - } &gt; SO_3^{2 - }$$.</p>",
