    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>Some complex ions of nitrogen show similarities with halide ions. These are called pseudohalide ions e.g., OCN<sup>$$-$$</sup>, NCO<sup>$$-$$</sup>, CN<sup>$$-$$</sup> etc.</p>\n<p>Halogens, among themselves, from complex ions which are called polyhalide ions. e.g., I$$_3^ - $$, Brl$$_2^ {-1} $$ etc.</p>\n<p>Similarly, interhalogens are the compounds of halogens in which one halogen is cation and other halogen is anion. e.g., IF<sub>7</sub>, ICI<sub>5</sub>, BrF<sub>5</sub>, IF<sub>5</sub> etc.</p>",
